  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dc0 \u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dda\u0dc2\u0dca\u0da7 \u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1 \u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0ddb\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd4\u0db6 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Chinese Prime Minister congratulates new Prime Minister Dinesh",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Chinese Prime Minister Li Keqiang has sent a message to the new Prime Minister of Sri Lanka, Mr. Dinesh Gunawardena, congratulating him.",
        "Li said in his message that China and Sri Lanka enjoy deep traditional friendship and are friendly neighbors and strategic partners.",
        "Li said that since the establishment of diplomatic relations 65 years ago, the two sides have always treated each other with respect and equality, continuously strengthened mutual political trust and promoted mutually beneficial cooperation and joined hands to deal with difficulties and challenges. Bilateral relations have maintained a strong and stable development.",
        "Li said the Chinese side strongly supports the friendly cooperation between China and Sri Lanka, sympathizes with the Sri Lankan people in the current difficulties they face, and is ready to continue to support and assist them in their capacity.",
        "The Chinese Premier said he is willing to work with Prime Minister Gunawardena to strengthen cooperation and mutual support among developing countries, deepen practical cooperation in various fields, and bring more benefits to the two countries and their people."
      ],
